Name: COMMITTED_PKT_ANY
Description: Thread committed a pkt. Packets executed

Name: AXI_LINE128_READ_REQUEST
Description: 128-byte line read requests issued by primary AXI master

Name: AXI_LINE128_WRITE_REQUEST
Description: 128-byte line write requests issued by primary AXI master

Name: L2FETCH_MISS
Description: L2fetch miss from a programed inquiry. Of the events qualified by 0x7E
column6: the ones that resulted in  L2 miss. i.e. the line was not previously allocated in the L2 cache and will be fetched from backing memory.

Name: IU_NO_PKT_PVIEW_CYCLES
Description: Cycles pmuDefines[200].cluster could not commit due to IQ being empty.

Name: HVX_LD_L2_OUTSTANDING
Description: Increments by 2 per cycle in 128-byte mode. Stall cycles due to load pending

Name: HVX_PKT
Description: Increments by 2 per packet in 128-byte mode. Packets with HVX instructions
